<h3>Now is the time</h3>
<p>BYU-Idaho's online degree program gives you the flexibility to finish your degree while balancing your busy life. Accelerate to graduation by taking classes year round or take a semester off when you need to. Not only will you enjoy the convenience of online courses but you'll find the same Spirit online that you felt on campus.</p>
<h3>How long do these programs take?</h3>
<p>Our online programs allow students the flexibility to finish their degree while balancing a busy life. Students can accelerate to graduation by taking courses year round, or take a semester off when needed. Students must complete Bachelor programs in eight years, and Associate programs within four years.</p>
<h3>What are the courses like?</h3>
<p>Online courses at BYU-Idaho follow a similar format and have the same learning objectives as campus-based courses. Students should expect to interact with each other and participate in the learning model. <a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/courses/explore">Learn more about BYU-Idaho courses online.</a></p>
<h3>Where do I begin?</h3>
<p>Students who meet the&nbsp;<a class="intLink" href="x43410.xml">admission requirements</a>&nbsp;can apply to be directly admitted into an online degree program. These students will start by taking the online orientation course (<a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/online-degrees-and-certificates/gs111">GS 111</a>), a one-credit course offered every block. This course prepares students to succeed online and charts a course to graduation. Pathway students who complete Academic Start do not need to take GS 111.</p>
